io.jenetics.prngine

Class Random64

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Random
      • io.jenetics.prngine.PRNG
        • io.jenetics.prngine.Random64
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    KISS64Random, LCG64ShiftRandom, MT19937_64Random, XOR64ShiftRandom

    public abstract class Random64
extends PRNG
    An abstract base class which eases the implementation of Random objects which natively creates random long values. All other Random functions are optimized using this long values. Subtypes of this class must only implement the nextLong() method. 
    
 final class MyRandom extends Random54 {
     public int nextLong() {
         return ...;
     }
 }
    A quicker way for creating a Random64 instance is using the static factory method of(LongSupplier). 
    
 final Random jrand = new Random();
 final Random64 random = Random64.of(jrand::nextLong);
